      <p>
        <s>The film <ref target="b10gk4_1" type="title">The Hate U Give</ref> directed by <ref target="b10gk4_1" type="director">George Tillmann Jr.</ref> <date>2018</date>, is about a girl, who fights for justice for black people, because her friend was killed by a police officer out of racism.</s>
        <s>The scene presents <ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Chris</ref> and <ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Starr</ref> talking about their relationship.</s>
        <s><ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Chris</ref> gives <ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Starr</ref> headphones <choice><orig>wich</orig><reg>which</reg></choice> play music, he made for her.</s>
        <s><ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Starr</ref> tells him, that she isn't ok with what <choice><orig>happend</orig><reg>happened</reg></choice> before.</s>
        <s><ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Chris</ref> says that he is sorry and complains that she hasn't enough time for him.</s>
        <s><ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Starr</ref> acts as she didn't like the music, so <ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Chris</ref> puts the headphones out of his <choice><orig>mobilphones</orig><reg>mobile phones</reg></choice> and starts dancing in the hallway.</s>
        <s><ref target="b10gk4_1" type="character">Starr</ref> smiles at him.</s>
